text: Kenneth William Tinegate (1915-1958), was a male rower who competed for England. ==Rowing career== He represented England and won a bronze medal in the double sculls with Jack Brown at the 1950 British Empire Games in Auckland, New Zealand. ==Personal life== During the Games in 1950 he lived at Oakfield Road, Selly Park, Birmingham and was a deputy manager. He was a member of the Birmingham Rowing Club. ==References== Category:1915 births Category:1958 deaths Category:English male rowers Category:Rowers at the 1950 British Empire Games Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in rowing Category:Commonwealth Games bronze medallists for England
